A dinner to raise funds for veteran journalist Louis Otieno was held at Villa Rosa hotel on Friday. Otieno is expected to undergo a cochlea implant. Present were Suba North MP Millie Mabone as the master of ceremony, governance consultant Cyprian Nyamwamu, advocate Alutalala Mukhwana and politician Alex Shipiri. The implant will be done in the country and among the doctors to take part will be Dr Mujahid Din from Cochlea Implant Group of Kenya.  Marketers Humphrey Slade Alwang'a and Alex Shipiri.  Rhythm City's Anne Muchoki and Rahab Foundation's Damaris Too.